WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:32.299 --> 00:00:33.832
            HOLD THE ELEVATOR !

3
00:00:39.039 --> 00:00:40.005
                         THANKS.

4
00:01:07.134 --> 00:01:08.366
       ( phone ringing )

5
00:01:32.025 --> 00:01:33.158
        I CAN'T DO IT.

6
00:01:33.226 --> 00:01:35.594
  LARRY DAVID.
 FOR DR. LYNCH.

7
00:01:44.905 --> 00:01:46.738
         MELISSA WINNAKER.
            OR WINOKER.

8
00:01:46.807 --> 00:01:47.906
     MARISSA.

9
00:01:47.975 --> 00:01:49.675
              OH. THAT'LL DO IT.

10
00:01:49.743 --> 00:01:50.776
 WINOKUR.

11
00:01:50.844 --> 00:01:52.010
                  THE FIRST DOOR
                   ON THE LEFT.

12
00:01:52.079 --> 00:01:53.444
             DOCTOR WILL SEE YOU
              IN JUST A MINUTE.

13
00:01:53.513 --> 00:01:55.080
GREAT. THANKS.
                 YOU'RE WELCOME.

14
00:02:00.354 --> 00:02:01.452
 EXCUSE ME.

15
00:02:01.521 --> 00:02:02.688
         CAN I HELP YOU ?

16
00:02:02.756 --> 00:02:03.955
COULD YOU PLEASE
     TELL ME

17
00:02:04.024 --> 00:02:06.758
WHAT TIME THAT WOMAN'S
 APPOINTMENT WAS FOR ?

18
00:02:07.727 --> 00:02:09.627
          MISS WINOKUR'S. 11:45.

19
00:02:11.932 --> 00:02:13.231
WELL. SHE'S AFTER ME.

20
00:02:13.300 --> 00:02:14.533
SHE'S SUPPOSED
TO BE AFTER ME.

21
00:02:14.602 --> 00:02:16.101
             WELL. SHE SIGNED IN
              BEFORE YOU. SIR.

22
00:02:16.169 --> 00:02:17.536
  I'M 11:30.
 SHE'S 11:45.

23
00:02:17.605 --> 00:02:19.104
WHY AREN'T I GOING
  AHEAD OF HER ?

24
00:02:19.172 --> 00:02:21.406
            SHE WAS HERE FIRST.
           SHE SIGNED IN FIRST.
            WE SAW HER FIRST--

25
00:02:21.474 --> 00:02:22.908
 AND MY APPOINTMENT
    IS FOR 11:30.

26
00:02:22.977 --> 00:02:25.143
        WELL. SIR. IT WAS JUST
       A FEW MINUTES BEFORE YOU.

27
00:02:25.212 --> 00:02:26.712
                 THERE'S NO NEED
                  TO GET UPSET.

28
00:02:26.780 --> 00:02:28.079
                WE HAVE A POLICY
                 IN THIS OFFICE

29
00:02:28.148 --> 00:02:29.614
               THAT YOU ARE SEEN
                AS YOU SIGN IN.

30
00:02:29.682 --> 00:02:31.016
               THAT'S THE POLICY
                OF THE OFFICE.

31
00:02:31.084 --> 00:02:32.184
   WHAT IS IT.
 LIKE A BAKERY ?

32
00:02:32.252 --> 00:02:34.219
 YOU PICK A NUMBER AND
THE FIRST NUMBER GOES ?

33
00:02:34.287 --> 00:02:35.954
                IT'S FIRST COME.
                  FIRST SERVE.

34
00:02:36.023 --> 00:02:38.223
   WHY DON'T YOU JUST
 HAVE A LITTLE TICKET ?
WE CAN ALL TAKE NUMBERS.

35
00:02:38.291 --> 00:02:39.791
  WHY EVEN GIVE OUT
 THE APPOINTMENTS ?

36
00:02:39.860 --> 00:02:41.426
                  SIR. JUST CALM
                   DOWN. PLEASE.

37
00:02:41.494 --> 00:02:43.461
  NO. SERIOUSLY. FOR
THIS POLICY. YOU DON'T
  NEED APPOINTMENTS.

38
00:02:43.530 --> 00:02:46.031
            SIR. THE POLICY OF
           THE OFFICE IS YOU ARE
           SEEN AS YOU COME IN.

39
00:02:46.099 --> 00:02:49.300
            THAT WAY. WE SEE
           AS MANY PATIENTS AS
        POSSIBLE IN A GIVEN DAY.

40
00:02:49.369 --> 00:02:50.601
               THAT MAKES SENSE.
                 DOESN'T IT ?

41
00:02:50.670 --> 00:02:51.703
 NO. IT DOESN'T.

42
00:02:51.772 --> 00:02:53.805
  IT DOESN'T MAKE
 ANY SENSE AT ALL.

43
00:02:53.874 --> 00:02:55.640
           I UNDERSTAND. YOU'RE
           PROBABLY HAVING A BAD
           DAY. YOU'RE IN PAIN.

44
00:02:55.708 --> 00:02:57.308
          BUT THAT IS THE POLICY
              OF THIS OFFICE.

45
00:02:57.377 --> 00:02:58.643
DO YOU UNDERSTAND
  THIS POLICY ?

46
00:02:58.712 --> 00:03:00.879
              PLEASE DON'T TALK
             TO HER. SHE'S BUSY.

47
00:03:03.216 --> 00:03:04.282
                       I GET IT.

48
00:03:04.351 --> 00:03:06.218
            IT'S NO SWISS PICNIC
               FOR ME. EITHER.

49
00:03:11.424 --> 00:03:12.790
                     ( sighing )

50
00:03:14.995 --> 00:03:16.294
             DID YOU HEAR THAT ?

51
00:03:18.032 --> 00:03:21.767
           UNBELIEVABLE. THIS IS
             THEIR POLICY. OK.

52
00:03:21.835 --> 00:03:25.336
       FIRST COME. FIRST SERVED.
          IT'S UNBELIEVABLE.

53
00:03:25.405 --> 00:03:27.438
                   DID YOU HEAR
                   ANY OF THAT ?

54
00:03:28.775 --> 00:03:30.575
      HUH ?

55
00:03:30.643 --> 00:03:31.943
        YEAH. NO.
      WE HEARD IT.

56
00:03:32.012 --> 00:03:34.079
  WE JUST FEEL LIKE IT'S
   NOT REALLY NECESSARY

57
00:03:34.147 --> 00:03:36.747
    TO COMMENT AT THIS
     PARTICULAR TIME.

58
00:03:36.816 --> 00:03:39.050
   NO COMMENT UNTIL
 THE TIME LIMIT IS UP.

59
00:03:43.924 --> 00:03:46.424
     IT DOESN'T MATTER WHAT TIME
      YOUR APPOINTMENT IS FOR.

60
00:03:46.493 --> 00:03:48.960
        ANYBODY WHO COMES IN
    AHEAD OF YOU GETS YOUR SPOT.

61
00:03:49.029 --> 00:03:50.828
                   THAT'S HOW
                THEY DO IT HERE.

62
00:03:50.898 --> 00:03:52.363
                I'M TELLING YOU.

63
00:03:53.267 --> 00:03:54.499
                          WHAT ?

64
00:03:54.567 --> 00:03:56.034
               WHAT DO YOU HAVE
               TO SAY. NOTHING ?

65
00:03:56.103 --> 00:03:58.369
             CAN'T TALK ? PEOPLE
             AT DOCTOR'S OFFICES
                 CAN'T TALK.

66
00:03:58.438 --> 00:03:59.704
                  IS THAT A RULE
                  OR SOMETHING ?

67
00:03:59.773 --> 00:04:02.107
                  OH. EXCUSE ME.

68
00:04:02.176 --> 00:04:05.010
        I'M SORRY TO BOTHER YOU.
          BUT. YOU KNOW. I DID
          A NICE THING FOR YOU.

69
00:04:05.078 --> 00:04:07.212
    I HELD THE ELEVATOR FOR YOU.
      SO YOU CAN GET ON FIRST.

70
00:04:07.280 --> 00:04:08.747
    RIGHT.

71
00:04:08.816 --> 00:04:10.081
                  AND THEN I WAS
                   A GENTLEMAN.
                  I LET YOU OUT.

72
00:04:10.150 --> 00:04:11.682
RIGHT.

73
00:04:11.751 --> 00:04:13.718
             AND YOU CAME DOWN
          THE HALL. YOU WOULDN'T
            LET ME GET BY YOU--

74
00:04:13.787 --> 00:04:15.720
I WOULDN'T LET
YOU GET BY ME ?

75
00:04:15.789 --> 00:04:16.922
                   YOU SIGNED IN
                   AHEAD OF ME.

76
00:04:16.991 --> 00:04:19.024
I WAS HERE BEFORE YOU. OF
COURSE I SIGNED IN AHEAD.

77
00:04:19.092 --> 00:04:21.359
        YEAH. BUT MY APPOINTMENT
             WAS FOR 11:30.
            YOURS FOR 11:45.

78
00:04:21.428 --> 00:04:23.094
 YOU KNOW WHAT TIME
MY APPOINTMENT WAS ?

79
00:04:23.163 --> 00:04:25.230
 WHY DO YOU EVEN
CARE WHAT TIME MY
APPOINTMENT WAS ?

80
00:04:25.298 --> 00:04:27.365
    WHAT WERE YOU DOING IN THERE
       ANYWAY FOR 40 MINUTES ?

81
00:04:27.434 --> 00:04:30.101
    WHAT WAS GOING ON IN THERE ?
      WHAT. WERE YOU CHATTING ?

82
00:04:30.170 --> 00:04:32.804
        TALKING ABOUT OLD TIMES.
             WHAT WAS THAT ?

83
00:04:32.873 --> 00:04:34.105
                           HUH ?

84
00:04:34.174 --> 00:04:35.573
                    YOU KNOW.
                 IT'S NOT RIGHT.

85
00:04:35.642 --> 00:04:37.408
                   YOU'RE IN
              A DOCTOR'S OFFICE.
                DON'T CHITCHAT.

86
00:04:37.477 --> 00:04:39.677
   DON'T ASK HIM
 HOW HIS DAY WAS.
YOU DON'T CHITCHAT.

87
00:04:39.746 --> 00:04:42.013
           YOU KNOW. LET HIM
       EXAMINE YOU. YOU GO OUT.

88
00:04:42.082 --> 00:04:44.582
           MR. DOBB. LURRY DOBB.

89
00:04:44.651 --> 00:04:45.951
 THAT'S LARRY DAVID.

90
00:04:46.019 --> 00:04:48.353
           MR. DAVID. THE DOCTOR
             WILL SEE YOU NOW.

91
00:04:48.421 --> 00:04:51.556
OH. WOW. THAT'S VERY
 SPECIAL. ISN'T IT ?

92
00:04:54.128 --> 00:04:55.193
 THANK YOU.

93
00:04:55.262 --> 00:04:56.394
                   THANK YOU FOR
                  YOUR PATIENCE.

94
00:04:56.463 --> 00:04:58.263
   YES. IT'S BEEN
 QUITE A NICE TIME.

95
00:04:58.331 --> 00:04:59.530
             RIGHT HERE. ROOM 4.

96
00:04:59.599 --> 00:05:01.767
    OH. WHAT'S THIS.
 ANOTHER HALF HOUR NOW ?

97
00:05:05.839 --> 00:05:06.838
 HEY. LARRY.

98
00:05:06.907 --> 00:05:08.639
             HEY. CAN I ASK
            YOU A QUESTION ?

99
00:05:08.708 --> 00:05:10.442
SURE. WHAT'S UP ?

100
00:05:10.510 --> 00:05:12.143
             WHAT'S WITH YOUR
           WAITING ROOM POLICY ?
          I DON'T GET IT AT ALL.

101
00:05:12.212 --> 00:05:14.579
    YOU KNOW WHAT ?
YOU'RE THE FIRST PERSON
 WHO HASN'T LIKED IT.

102
00:05:14.647 --> 00:05:15.947
              NOBODY'S MENTIONED
                 THIS TO YOU ?

103
00:05:16.016 --> 00:05:17.148
 NO. THEY LOVE IT.

104
00:05:17.217 --> 00:05:18.749
            WELL. YOU GOTTA DO
           SOMETHING ABOUT THIS.

105
00:05:18.818 --> 00:05:19.951
                      I MEAN.
                   IT'S REALLY--

106
00:05:20.020 --> 00:05:22.587
HEY. I'LL MAKE A NOTE.
   I'LL MAKE A NOTE.

107
00:05:22.655 --> 00:05:24.055
               I'VE BEEN WAITING
                   SO LONG.

108
00:05:24.124 --> 00:05:26.124
     I'M LATE FOR AN APPOINTMENT
         WITH DIANE KEATON.

109
00:05:26.193 --> 00:05:27.492
                 AND IT'S A VERY
                IMPORTANT THING.

110
00:05:27.560 --> 00:05:28.593
DIANE KEATON ?
                           YEAH.

111
00:05:28.661 --> 00:05:29.895
WHAT IS THAT ABOUT ?

112
00:05:29.963 --> 00:05:31.963
           SHE'S VERY INTERESTED
            IN DOING MY SCRIPT.

113
00:05:32.032 --> 00:05:34.199
GOOD FOR YOU. LARRY.
HEY. THAT'S EXCITING.

114
00:05:34.267 --> 00:05:35.266
                     YEAH.

115
00:05:35.335 --> 00:05:36.334
WOW.

116
00:05:36.403 --> 00:05:38.536
       THE SCRIPT THAT
        MY WIFE READ.

117
00:05:38.605 --> 00:05:39.537
                   SHE READ IT ?

118
00:05:39.606 --> 00:05:40.671
MY WIFE READ
THAT SCRIPT.

119
00:05:40.740 --> 00:05:42.307
YES. YES.

120
00:05:45.612 --> 00:05:47.378
                DID SHE SAY
                ANYTHING ?

121
00:05:47.981 --> 00:05:49.214
 NO. NO. NO.

122
00:05:49.283 --> 00:05:52.117
 SHE READ IT. THOUGH.
 I SAW HER READING IT.

123
00:05:52.185 --> 00:05:53.485
            SHE'S A GOOD LAWYER.

124
00:05:53.553 --> 00:05:54.986
YEAH. GOOD LAWYER.

125
00:05:55.055 --> 00:05:56.754
 WELL. WHAT DO YOU
GOT FOR ME TODAY ?
   WHAT'S THIS ?

126
00:05:56.823 --> 00:05:58.223
                    OH. I JAMMED
                     MY FINGER.

127
00:05:58.291 --> 00:05:59.457
HOW'D YOU DO THAT ?

128
00:05:59.526 --> 00:06:01.026
          YOU KNOW THE COMEDIAN.
              RICHARD LEWIS ?

129
00:06:01.094 --> 00:06:02.594
SURE.

130
00:06:02.662 --> 00:06:05.097
            WE HAD A FIGHT OVER
          SOME BRACELET IN FRONT
            OF A JEWELRY STORE.

131
00:06:05.165 --> 00:06:07.765
YEAH. HOW DOES THAT FEEL ?
    YOU OK WITH THAT ?

132
00:06:07.834 --> 00:06:08.867
AND HOW ABOUT THAT ?

133
00:06:08.936 --> 00:06:09.901
                YEAH. IT'S FINE.

134
00:06:09.970 --> 00:06:10.969
WHAT IS THIS ?

135
00:06:11.038 --> 00:06:12.070
                  IT'S-- MY WIFE
                  MADE A SPLINT.

136
00:06:12.139 --> 00:06:13.138
 YOUR WIFE ?

137
00:06:13.206 --> 00:06:14.405
IT'S A PLASTIC KNIFE.

138
00:06:14.474 --> 00:06:16.407
  WERE YOU AT A PICNIC
WHEN YOU HURT YOURSELF ?

139
00:06:16.476 --> 00:06:17.708
                   HA. HA.

140
00:06:17.777 --> 00:06:19.477
 NOTHING HURTS.
 YOU'RE ALL SET.
LOSE THE SPLINT.

141
00:06:19.546 --> 00:06:21.612
  UNLESS YOU SAVED THE FORK
AND YOU GOT YOURSELF A PAIR.

142
00:06:21.681 --> 00:06:22.748
            ALL RIGHT. LARRY.
                 SEE YA.

143
00:06:22.816 --> 00:06:24.850
           DO I HAVE TO
          PAY FOR THIS ?

144
00:06:29.823 --> 00:06:30.755
 HELLO.

145
00:06:30.823 --> 00:06:31.823
                             HI.

146
00:06:34.894 --> 00:06:36.461
             OK. THAT'S $3.

147
00:06:41.801 --> 00:06:43.501
              UH-OH.
              UH-OH.

148
00:06:43.570 --> 00:06:45.036
                   I NEED $3.

149
00:06:45.105 --> 00:06:46.604
   I DON'T THINK
 I HAVE ANY MONEY.

150
00:06:46.673 --> 00:06:48.606
           DID YOU LOOK IN YOUR
           LITTLE CHANGE THING ?

151
00:06:48.675 --> 00:06:51.442
  I DON'T HAVE IT. IT
WOULD BE IN MY WALLET.

152
00:06:51.511 --> 00:06:53.678
           MY DRAWER NEEDS $3.
          I'M SORRY. YOU KNOW.

153
00:06:53.746 --> 00:06:55.646
 I KNOW. YOU KNOW WHAT ?
    MY LAWYER'S HERE.

154
00:06:55.715 --> 00:06:57.615
    MY DOCTOR'S HERE.
 I'LL BE BACK ON FRIDAY.

155
00:06:57.684 --> 00:06:59.284
               OK. I HEAR THAT
                ALL THE TIME.

156
00:06:59.352 --> 00:07:00.585
           I NEED THE MONEY.

157
00:07:00.654 --> 00:07:01.920
      CAN YOU LAY IT
       OUT FOR ME ?

158
00:07:01.989 --> 00:07:03.020
             YOU DON'T HAVE $3 ?

159
00:07:03.090 --> 00:07:05.022
 I DON'T HAVE IT.
 I'M OUT OF CASH.

160
00:07:05.092 --> 00:07:06.157
I'M AN HONEST PERSON.

161
00:07:06.226 --> 00:07:07.592
I'LL PAY YOU BACK.
    I PROMISE.

162
00:07:07.660 --> 00:07:10.195
       I'LL PAY YOU
       BACK $5. OK ?

163
00:07:10.264 --> 00:07:12.630
I'LL GIVE YOU $5 BACK
ON FRIDAY. I PROMISE.

164
00:07:12.699 --> 00:07:14.465
                DO YOU PROMISE ?
I PROMISE.

165
00:07:14.534 --> 00:07:16.501
 WILL YOU BE HERE
    ON FRIDAY ?

166
00:07:16.569 --> 00:07:17.602
            YES. I WILL BE HERE.

167
00:07:17.670 --> 00:07:19.104
 OK. I WILL PAY
 YOU ON FRIDAY.

168
00:07:19.172 --> 00:07:20.371
           I RECOGNIZE YOU. OK ?

169
00:07:20.440 --> 00:07:21.907
 PLEASE BELIEVE ME. OK ?

170
00:07:21.975 --> 00:07:25.210
         THIS MY OWN MONEY.
         I PUT IT IN DRAWER.
         OK. YOU OWE ME $3.

171
00:07:25.278 --> 00:07:27.112
DO YOU BELIEVE ME ?
                      YEAH.

172
00:07:27.180 --> 00:07:28.479
I WILL PAY YOU.
                    YOU BETTER.

173
00:07:28.548 --> 00:07:30.915
      I WILL. OK. THANK
       YOU VERY MUCH.

174
00:07:30.983 --> 00:07:31.917
       THANK YOU.

175
00:07:31.985 --> 00:07:33.684
                        WELCOME.

176
00:07:33.753 --> 00:07:35.620
        HEY. I REMEMBER
          YOUR FACE !

177
00:07:46.233 --> 00:07:47.298
                            HEY.

178
00:07:49.369 --> 00:07:51.536
                 YEAH. SHE LEFT.

179
00:07:51.604 --> 00:07:52.637
           OH.

180
00:07:54.807 --> 00:07:56.441
               I KEPT HER HERE
             AS LONG AS I COULD.

181
00:07:56.509 --> 00:07:57.542
                 WHAT HAPPENED ?

182
00:07:57.610 --> 00:07:59.511
  I GOT HELD UP AT
 A DOCTOR'S OFFICE.

183
00:07:59.579 --> 00:08:00.611
               ARE YOU OK ?

184
00:08:00.680 --> 00:08:02.047
    LET ME TELL YOU
      SOMETHING.

185
00:08:02.115 --> 00:08:03.614
       MY DAYS OF
   ELEVATOR ETIQUETTE
        ARE OVER.

186
00:08:03.683 --> 00:08:04.682
        OVER.

187
00:08:04.751 --> 00:08:06.384
    I'M NOT HOLDING
    DOORS ANYMORE.

188
00:08:06.453 --> 00:08:08.486
   NOT LETTING WOMEN OUT
FIRST ANYMORE. THAT'S DONE.

189
00:08:08.555 --> 00:08:10.322
            I HAVE NO IDEA WHAT
           YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

190
00:08:10.390 --> 00:08:12.023
  WELL. THAT'S WHAT
CAUSED ME TO BE LATE.

191
00:08:12.092 --> 00:08:14.292
'CAUSE I LET A WOMAN OUT FIRST
   AND SHE GOT IN THE OFFICE

192
00:08:14.361 --> 00:08:15.693
 AND TOOK 45 MINUTES
     AND. UH...

193
00:08:15.762 --> 00:08:17.795
           NO. I DON'T KNOW WHAT
          TO TELL YOU. SHE SAID.

194
00:08:17.864 --> 00:08:20.465
          "I DON'T KNOW IF I CAN
            WORK WITH SOMEBODY
          WHO'S LATE LIKE THIS."

195
00:08:20.534 --> 00:08:21.466
 SHE SAID THAT ?

196
00:08:21.534 --> 00:08:22.567
          SHE'S NOT GONNA DO IT.

197
00:08:22.635 --> 00:08:24.269
             THAT'S ALL. I MEAN.
             I DON'T MEAN TO...

198
00:08:24.337 --> 00:08:25.636
            WHAT ARE YOU DOING ?

199
00:08:25.705 --> 00:08:26.937
 I'M TESTING MY FINGER.

200
00:08:27.006 --> 00:08:28.806
                      ALL RIGHT.

201
00:08:28.875 --> 00:08:30.908
       WELL. ALL I'M TELLING YOU
       IS. IT DOESN'T LOOK GOOD.

202
00:08:30.977 --> 00:08:32.243
 I CAN'T CALL HER ?

203
00:08:32.312 --> 00:08:33.911
           YOU KNOW WHAT ?
     I SUGGEST YOU WRITE A NOTE.

204
00:08:33.980 --> 00:08:35.480
      I'M WRITING
     LIKE TARZAN.

205
00:08:35.548 --> 00:08:36.947
 YOU KNOW. I CAN'T.

206
00:08:37.016 --> 00:08:39.617
        WELL TRY. IT DOESN'T
        LOOK GOOD. THAT'S ALL
         I'M SAYING TO YOU.

207
00:08:40.520 --> 00:08:42.287
           IT DOESN'T LOOK GOOD.

208
00:08:42.355 --> 00:08:43.688
 THIS HER TEA ?

209
00:08:43.756 --> 00:08:45.190
                 THAT'S HER TEA.

210
00:08:45.258 --> 00:08:47.725
 OH. SHE'S SO PERFECT
 FOR THIS THING. TOO.

211
00:08:47.794 --> 00:08:49.627
         PERFECT.

212
00:08:49.696 --> 00:08:51.762
               I KNOW. WELL.
           WE'LL TRY. WE'LL TRY.
          I'M NOT GONNA GIVE UP.

213
00:08:51.831 --> 00:08:53.264
                   YOU WANT
              SOMETHING TO EAT ?

214
00:08:53.333 --> 00:08:54.832
      I'M JUST GONNA
        GET GOING.

215
00:08:55.435 --> 00:08:56.501
                      ALL RIGHT.

216
00:08:56.569 --> 00:08:58.936
OH. YOU KNOW WHAT ? DO
 YOU HAVE ANY MONEY ?

217
00:09:12.552 --> 00:09:13.551
HEY.

218
00:09:13.620 --> 00:09:15.387
        HI. YOU'RE JUST IN TIME.

219
00:09:15.455 --> 00:09:20.225
 I'D LIKE YOU TO MEET OUR NEW
  INTERIOR DECORATOR. CARMEN.

220
00:09:21.394 --> 00:09:23.694
               HE'S SURPRISED.
            YOU DON'T TELL HIM ?

221
00:09:23.763 --> 00:09:25.630
    NO. NO. I HEARD
 RUMBLINGS ABOUT IT--

222
00:09:25.698 --> 00:09:27.632
            RELAX. YOU ARE IN
         GOOD HANDS. BELIEVE ME.

223
00:09:27.700 --> 00:09:29.800
 AM I. REALLY ?
 I'VE HEARD THAT
